A shell that can run scripts.

Purpose:
To simplify the testing work. You can use this shell instead of the original one.

Usage:
sh [script]

Author:
Xiangru Chen

History:
2008-11-21 Xiangru Chen: The first version.

Arguments:
script: the name of the script file.
If you call sh without arguments, it will act no different to the original shell.
When a script file is specified, it will run the commands in the script as if you type them in the prompt.

A sample script:
	sample.sh:
	[
		echo this is a script
		matmult &
		matmult &
		matmult &
		matmult &
		matmult
	]
